<br>
   Any exp I get is usually negated by the loss from wipeouts.<br>
It is extrordinarlily rare anything drops I even want and if it did I would be outbid.<br>
      Experince groups are primarily how you advance your character by gaining levels or AAXP.<br>
<br>
    I seem to be always wasting time LFG.<br>
I just wonder Is, are their a guilds (on this server) whose primary focus is grouping together with other guildmates for exp.<br>
<br>
     Am, I weird or asking too much, for thinking grouping together should be the number one priority of at least one decent size level 60+ guild.<br>
<br>
        I quit my first guild because a group of 5 guildmates,  chose a non-guild member to join there group because that characters class was slightly more advantageous to the group than mine. They invite this non-guild person, and all go running off to SEB and I am left spending the next hour LFG.<br>
    The second guild I was in, disolved. But I remember the guild leaders preaching; 'its not the guilds job to help you find a group.'  The group leaders all grouped together but never had a space for anyone else in guild.<br>
<br>
       I have asked a number of people in different guilds, and they always say &quot;we group with other guild members when we can&quot;<br>
I guess I am looking for more of a focus on grouping than that.<br>
I do not think it is asking to much that if a guild member logs on and is having difficulty finding a group; and you are in a group with say 4 guildmates and 2 people from other guilds, that the four of you excuse your self from the group and then start a new group including the guild mate who was lfg.<br>
or<br>
that you log on and wait 10 or 15 minutes for other guildmates to logon so you can form a guild group.  <br>
<br>
       I wonder why guilds do not work out some schedule for guild members to log on at a set time and form guild groups.<br>
<br>
    I know one thing that makes this a problem more difficult, is everyones play schedule is diiferent, time zone, start time and play lengeth are rarely the same.<br>
    Also no matter how good the intentions a small guild has a problem having enough players of the same level on at the same times day after day.<br>
<br>
          This is just my impression, and frustration.  I would love to be able to log on 5 nights a week at 8:30 EST and be able to find a group quickly and start racking up exp for the next 3 or 4 hours; but I have been unable to accomplish this. <br>
