<br>
But level dispersement does play a factor I know.  With my guild, we went from a mid-high 50's guild to a mid 40's guild within a few weeks time.  We're teaching the younger crew how to raid so hopefully in several months we will be close to where we were strength wise.  Once you hit 61, exp outside of PoP doesn't happen as often - in Fungus at 62, almost all mobs turn light blue to you.  That forces the higher lvl folks to group in different places than than younger folk, where as before you could still group together.<br>
<br>
Now, 60+ are getting flagged for tier 2 zones, which other folks are struggling in tier 1 zones.<br>
<br>
It does seem that there are no high level guilds that are not raiding guild; like Elder Servitor's non-NBG motto, it is a new concept and one I bet a number of other folks would be interested in.  <br>
<br>
You might have just found a pocket of opportunity.<br>
<br>
